This paper deals with approximate inference in probabilistic graphical models, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses heuristics for improving the accuracy of the approximation, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of iterative belief propagation and dual decomposition also suggests that this paper could be categorized under distributed systems (cs.DS) or control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with optimization techniques, which could place it under information theory (cs.IT).
